slashtime
------------------------------------------
Slashtime is a small program which displays the time in various places. 
It has a compact display of locations along with supporting information 
such as the date and the abbreviated code used to name that timezone.

Runtime requirements:
  jamvm-1.5.3-1
  java-gnome4.0-4.0.14-1

Build requirements:
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.10-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://research.operationaldynamics.com/projects/slashtime/

Canonical download:
  http://research.operationaldynamics.com/projects/slashtime/dist/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack slashtime-0.5.11-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./slashtime-0.5.11-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/slashtime-0.5.11-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/slashtime-0.5.11-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Port Notes:

